[{},{"attrs":{"title":"API: The watch Property","description":"The watch property lets you watch custom files for restarting the server."},"body":"<h1><a id=\"the-watch-property\" class=\"anchor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" href=\"#the-watch-property\"><svg version=\"1.1\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" class=\"octicon octicon-link\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"/></svg></a>The watch Property</h1><ul>\n<li>Type: <code>Object</code></li>\n<li>Default: <code>[]</code></li>\n</ul>\n<blockquote>\n<p>The watch property lets you watch custom files for restarting the server.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<pre><code class=\"hljs js\">watch: [<span class=\"hljs-string\">'~/custom/*.js'</span>]</code></pre><p><a href=\"https://github.com/paulmillr/chokidar\">chokidar</a> is used to set up the watchers. To learn more about chokidar&#39;s pattern options, see the <a href=\"https://github.com/paulmillr/chokidar#api\">chokidar API</a>.</p>\n","docLink":"https://github.com/nuxt/docs/blob/master/en/api/configuration-watch.md"}]